---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About HUGE Magazine"
  description="We exist for one reason: to make complex, world-changing ideas accessible and exciting for the people who need to understand them."
>
  <Header />

  <main class="about-main">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="content-width">
        <h1>About HUGE Magazine</h1>

        <p class="lead">
          HUGE Magazine is the definitive destination for breakthrough ideas, emerging technologies,
          and the innovations shaping tomorrow. We cover what's next before it's mainstream, with the
          editorial rigor of MIT Technology Review and the visual audacity of Wired.
        </p>

        <h2>What We Are</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>A magazine about <strong>ideas</strong>, not products</li>
          <li>A publication that assumes reader sophistication without requiring expertise</li>
          <li>A visual experience where design is co-equal with writing</li>
          <li>An authority that takes positions, not a stenographer of competing views</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>What We're Not</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>A tech news aggregator</li>
          <li>A gadget review site</li>
          <li>A startup cheerleader</li>
          <li>An AI hype machine</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Our Mission</h2>
        <p>
          We exist for one reason: <strong>to make complex, world-changing ideas accessible and
          exciting for the people who need to understand them.</strong>
        </p>

        <p>
          Whether you're a tech executive, innovation manager, researcher, or intellectually curious
          professional in any field, HUGE Magazine helps you understand where the world is going —
          not just what's trending today.
        </p>

        <h2>Editorial Philosophy</h2>
        <p>
          We sound like a brilliant friend who happens to work in tech — someone who can explain
          quantum computing over dinner without being condescending, and who has strong opinions
          about what it means for the world.
        </p>

        <p>We are:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Confident, not arrogant</strong> — We take positions. We make calls. We don't hedge everything.</li>
          <li><strong>Accessible, not dumbed-down</strong> — We explain complex ideas clearly without patronizing.</li>
          <li><strong>Opinionated, not preachy</strong> — We have a point of view. We don't lecture.</li>
          <li><strong>Curious, not credulous</strong> — We're excited about innovation but skeptical of hype.</li>
          <li><strong>Visual, not decorative</strong> — Design serves storytelling. Every image earns its place.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>What We Cover</h2>
        <div class="pillars">
          <div class="pillar">
            <h3>Breakthrough Technologies</h3>
            <p>Deep dives into AI/ML, quantum computing, biotech, clean energy, materials science, and more.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="pillar">
            <h3>HUGE Ideas</h3>
            <p>Weekly spotlight on breakthrough concepts, companies, or people creating massive impact.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="pillar">
            <h3>Innovation Case Studies</h3>
            <p>How breakthroughs actually happen — the messy, nonlinear reality of turning ideas into impact.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="pillar">
            <h3>Visionary Profiles</h3>
            <p>In-depth conversations with the people driving breakthrough thinking.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="pillar">
            <h3>Future Dispatches</h3>
            <p>Sharp, provocative takes on technology's intersection with society, policy, and culture.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Questions? Story ideas? Want to contribute?<br>
          <a href="/contact">Get in touch</a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about-main {
    padding: var(--space-2xl) 0;
    min-height: 80vh;
  }

  .lead {
    font-size: 1.35rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: rgba(13, 13, 13, 0.8);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  h1 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  }

  h2 {
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
    color: var(--color-electric-blue);
  }

  h3 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .pillars {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-lg);
    margin: var(--space-xl) 0;
  }

  .pillar {
    padding: var(--space-md);
    border: 1px solid rgba(13, 13, 13, 0.1);
    border-radius: 8px;
    background: rgba(0, 102, 255, 0.02);
  }

  .pillar h3 {
    color: var(--color-huge-black);
  }

  .pillar p {
    margin-bottom: 0;
    color: rgba(13, 13, 13, 0.7);
  }
</style>
